{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κάλλος</b>, εος, <br /> <i>Attic dialect</i> ους, τό, (καλός) <b>beauty</b>, especially of body, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.130, 20.235, etc.; κάλλεΐ τε στίλβων καὶ εἵμασιν 3.392; κάλλεϊ καὶ Χάρισι στίλβων 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.237; περί τ᾽ ἀμφί τε κ. ἄητο “hymnus ad Cererem” 276 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: in a concrete sense, as though external to the body, κάλλεϊ μέν οἱ πρῶτα προσώπατα καλὰ κάθηρεν ἀμβροσίῳ, οἵῳ Κυθέρεια Χρίεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.192: frequently in Trag. and Prose, γυναῖκε.. κάλλει ἀμώμω 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 185; κ. σώματος 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 105 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to αἶσχος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 201a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in a general sense, τῶν ἔργων τῷ μεγέθει καὶ τῷ κάλλει Χαλεπὸν ἐξισῶσαι τοὺς ἐπαίνους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.36; Χώρη κάλλεϊ καὶ ἀρετῇ μέγα ὑπερφέρουσα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.144, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Charmides” 157e, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 1.30 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of ships, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus [3.17]; ἀρετὴ ἂν εἴη κ. ψυχῆς 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 444d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ τῶν μαθημάτων κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Grg.” 475a \">Refs</a>]; ἐς κάλλος with an eye to <b>beauty</b>, so as to set off her <b>beauty</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 1073 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ γὰρ ἐς κ. τύχας δαίμων δίδωσιν so as to regard <b>beauty</b> or <b>show</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tr.” 1201 \">Refs</a>]; ὁ εἰς κ. βίος, opposed to αἰσχρουργία, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Agesilaus” 9.1; ἐς κ. ζῆν [prev. author] “Cyr.” 8.1.33 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but ἐς κ. κυνηγετεῖν hunt for <b>pleasure</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Cynegeticus” 25.9: in _plural_, σωμάτων κάλλη, opposed to ψυχῶν ἀρετή, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 112e. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> concrete, of persons, κ. κακῶν ὕπουλον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1396 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of a bird, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Clitarchus Gnomologus 21 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] codices; mostly of women, <b>a beauty</b>, τὴν θυγατέρα, δεινόν τι κάλλος καὶ μέγεθος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.2.7; Γαλάτεια, κάλλος Ἐρώτων 3rd c.BC: Philoxenus Epigrammaticus 8 (nisi to be read θάλος); Ἑλένη καὶ Λήδα καὶ ὅλως τὰ ἀρχαῖα κάλλη 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DMort.” 18.1, compare “Im.” 2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> in <i>plural</i>, <b>beautiful things</b>, as garments and stuffs, ἐν ποικίλοις.. κάλλεσιν βαίνειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 923 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; βάπτειν τὰ κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 333, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 110a, 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 7.63, 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus see entry ; κυπαρίττων ὕψη καὶ κάλλη 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 625c; μεγέθεσιν κάλλεσίν τε ἔργων [prev. author] “Criti.” 115d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ κ. τῆς ἑρμηνείας <b>beauties</b> of style, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor 5.1 (also in _sing._, τὸ κ. τῆς ἑρμ. 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 3)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; κάλλεα κηροῦ <b>beautiful works</b> of wax, i.e. honeycombs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 9.363.15 (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus); κάλλη τοιαῦτα καὶ τοσαῦτα ἱερῶν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 3.25 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; κ. οἰκοδομημάτων, ={καλὰ οἰκοδομήματα}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.409a, compare 935a, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 65.15. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Pythagoras Philosophus \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] name for <b>six</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Iamblichus Philosophus “in Nicomachi arithmeticam introductionem” p.34 P. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7782","accentedUnicode":"κάλλος","shortDef":"beauty","mediumDef":"beauty","stepGloss":"beauty","stepTransliteration":"kallos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}